        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 42–46. Comparison of the E Pacific Archierato species (the shells are equally sized for better comparison, consider, e.g., Tab. 1 for their real dimension). 42. A. michaelmonti, holotype. 43. A. rhondae, holotype. 44. A. panamaensis, lectotype. 45. A. columbella, neotype. 46. A. galapagensis, holotype." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4407247/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407222>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 7–9. Archierato type specimens. 7. Archierato maugeriae (Gray in Sowerby I, 1832) lectotype NHMUK 197410/1, L 5.2 mm “Levy County, Florida, U.S.A.” (courtesy H. Taylor). 8. Archierato columbella (Menke, 1847) neotype LACM 3302, L 6.8 mm, White Port, Los Angeles County, California, USA (courtesy L.T. Groves). 9. Archierato panamaensis (Carpenter, 1856) lectotype NHMUK 1966619/1, L 7.5 mm, ‘Pacific Panama’ (courtesy H. Taylor)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4407222/files/figure.png" .

